=== 公元前7年 ===
[[约翰内斯·开普勒|约翰内斯·开普勒]]在研究1603年的大合相时，认为[[伯利恒之星|伯利恒之星]]可能正是当年的大合相。他计算发现，木星和土星的三重合相发生在公元前7年（用[[天文計年|天文年号]]表示为-6）；<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Kepler and the Star of Bethlehem|url=http://adsabs.harvard.edu/full/1937JRASC..31..417B|last=Burke-Gaffney|first=W.|journal=Journal of the Royal Astronomical Society of Canada|accessdate=2020-05-27|year=1937|volume=31|page=417|bibcode=1937JRASC..31..417B|archive-date=2021-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105012726/http://adsabs.harvard.edu/full/1937JRASC..31..417B|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|first=Michael R.|last=Molnar|title=The Star of Bethlehem: The Legacy of the Magi|publisher=Rutgers University Press|year=1999}}</ref>三重合相是指木星和土星在[[衝_(天體位置)|冲日]]位置或其附近时的合相。在这种情况下，木星和土星将三次占据相同的赤道经线或黄道经线——取决于人们使用哪种“合相”的定义。这一现象由[[順行和逆行#視逆行運動|视逆行运动]]导致，发生在数月内。最近的三重合相发生在1980年和1981年<ref name="auto2">{{Cite web|title=The December 2020 Great Conjunction|url=https://www.timeanddate.com/astronomy/planets/great-conjunction|accessdate=2020-12-10|author=Jones|first=Graham|work=timeanddate.com|language=en|archive-date=2021-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210223044335/https://www.timeanddate.com/astronomy/planets/great-conjunction|dead-url=no}}</ref>，下一次将发生在2238年和2239年。

=== 1563年 ===
来自[[亞捷隆大學|克拉科夫学院]]的天文学家（{{link-en|扬·穆塞修斯|Jan Muscenius}}、斯坦尼斯瓦夫·雅各布奇克（Stanisław Jakobejusz）、尼古劳斯·谢德克（Nicolaus Schadeck）、彼得鲁斯·普罗博科维奇（Petrus Probosczowicze）等人）观测了1563年的大合相，以比较[[阿方索星曆表|阿方索星历表]]（基于[[地心说|地心说模型]]）和[[普魯士星曆表|普鲁士星历表]]（基于{{link-en|哥白尼体系|Copernican heliocentrism|哥白尼日心说}}）。根据普鲁士表，天文学家发现木星和土星彼此距离很近，以至于木星掩蔽了土星<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|last=Kesten|first=Hermann|title=Copernicus and his World|publisher=New York: Roy Publishers|year=1945|isbn=|location=|pages=320}}</ref>（1563年8月25日的实际角距离为6.8分<ref name="auto3" />）。而按照阿方索表，合相发生在另外一天，但在其预测的那一天里，角距离足足有141分。克拉科夫的教授们因而推荐采用更准确的哥白尼预测。在1578年至1580年期间，瓦伦丁·丰塔尼（Valentin Fontani）曾为哥白尼日心说发表了三次演说。

=== 2020年 ===
[[File:Jupiter_saturn_separation_2020_Dec.png|缩略图]]
2020年的大合相是自1623年以来最接近的一次<ref name="auto1" /><ref name="auto3" />，也是公元前三千年中第八近的一次，两颗行星间的最小距离为6.1[[弧分|角分]]。这次大合相也是自1226年以来最容易看到的近合相（因为之前1563年和1623年的近合相离太阳更近，因此更难看到）。<ref name="witness">{{Cite web|title=Witness the Great Conjunction of Jupiter and Saturn on December 21st|url=https://www.wcia.com/news/witness-the-great-conjunction-of-jupiter-and-saturn-on-december-21st/|accessdate=20 December 2020|author=Jacob Dickey|date=6 December 2020|publisher=WCIA|archive-date=2020-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201230063821/https://www.wcia.com/news/witness-the-great-conjunction-of-jupiter-and-saturn-on-december-21st/|dead-url=no}}</ref>它发生在日心合相的7周后，当时木星和土星的日心经度相同。<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020, November 2: Jupiter – Saturn Heliocentric Conjunction|url=https://whenthecurveslineup.com/2020/09/11/2020-november-2-jupiter-saturn-heliocentric-conjunction/|accessdate=2020-10-29|author=Hunt|date=2020-09-11|first=Jeffrey L.|work=When the Curves Line Up|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202000705/https://whenthecurveslineup.com/2020/09/11/2020-november-2-jupiter-saturn-heliocentric-conjunction/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

合相距离最近的时刻为协调世界时12月21日18时22分，<ref name="auto2" />当时木星在土星以南0.1°，太阳以东30°。这意味着这两颗行星一起出现在大多数中小型望远镜的视野中（尽管在没有光学辅助设备的情况下仍能将它们区分开）。<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020: December 21: The Great Conjunction of Jupiter and Saturn|url=https://whenthecurveslineup.com/2019/12/11/2020-december-21-the-great-conjunction-of-jupiter-and-saturn/|accessdate=2020-08-11|date=2019-12-11|work=When the Curves Line Up|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126053319/https://whenthecurveslineup.com/2019/12/11/2020-december-21-the-great-conjunction-of-jupiter-and-saturn/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在距离最近之时，两颗行星在肉眼看来呈一对联星。<ref name="witness" />在中北纬地区，日落后一小时可在西南地平线上方不到15°的高度，朝[[摩羯座|摩羯座]]的方向上看到这两颗行星。<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020: December 21: The Great Conjunction of Jupiter and Saturn|url=https://whenthecurveslineup.com/2019/12/11/2020-december-21-the-great-conjunction-of-jupiter-and-saturn/|accessdate=2020-08-27|author=Hunt|date=2019-12-11|first=Jeffrey L.|work=When the Curves Line Up|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126053319/https://whenthecurveslineup.com/2019/12/11/2020-december-21-the-great-conjunction-of-jupiter-and-saturn/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=5 upcoming conjunctions visible in the night sky, and how to see them|url=https://www.skyatnightmagazine.com/advice/skills/conjunctions-in-night-sky-how-see/|accessdate=2020-08-17|archive-date=2021-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301133537/https://www.skyatnightmagazine.com/advice/skills/conjunctions-in-night-sky-how-see/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

这次大合相引起了媒体的极大关注，由于合相发生在[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]前后，新闻界称其为“圣诞之星”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Starwatch: 'Christmas star' is the closest great conjunction in almost 400 years|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/dec/14/starwatch-christmas-star-closest-great-conjunction-400-years-jupiter-saturn|author=Clark|date=14 December 2020|first=Stuart|access-date=2020-12-26|archive-date=2021-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105025355/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/dec/14/starwatch-christmas-star-closest-great-conjunction-400-years-jupiter-saturn|dead-url=no}}</ref>

